<subSubSection lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="368" pageId="10" pageNumber="367" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,1986,2013]" lastBlockId="11.[151,1437,150,356]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="368" pageId="10" pageNumber="367">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1986,2012]" pageId="10" pageNumber="367">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The male genitalia of this species are similar to those of 
<taxonomicName authority="Park &amp; De Prins, 2019" authorityName="Park &amp; De Prins" authorityYear="2019" box="[936,1344,1986,2013]" class="Insecta" family="Lecithoceridae" genus="Thubdora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="367" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ealaensis">
<emphasis box="[936,1070,1986,2012]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="367">T. ealaensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Park, K. - T. &amp; De Prins, W." box="[1079,1344,1986,2013]" pageId="10" pageNumber="367" pagination="451 - 476" refId="ref10075" refString="Park, K. - T. &amp; De Prins, W. (2019) Re-examination of the type specimens of Lecithoceridae (Lepidoptera, Gelechioidea) deposited in the Royal Museum for Central Africa, Belgium, with descriptions of ten new species from DR Congo belonging to Torodora Meyrick and Thubdora Park. Zootaxa, 4571 4), 451 - 476. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4571.4.1" type="journal article" year="2019">Park &amp; De Prins, 2019</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but the apex of cucullus is slightly pointed whereas in the latter it is nearly parallel-sided. The yellowish costal patch on the forewing is very small and obscure. The abdominal segment VIII with V-shaped sclerite dorsally; a pair of hair pencil well-developed; sternite uniquely modified as shown in 
<figureCitation box="[856,943,222,248]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1675,1699]" captionTargetBox="[151,1408,381,1638]" captionTargetId="figure-116@11.[151,1436,380,1652]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 8. Thubdora vernaculella Park &amp; Karisch, 2021: A, Adult; B, Male genitalia, GU-3899/Karisch; B1, Aedeagus; C, Subgenital segments, in SDEI." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810524" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810524/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="368">Fig. 8C</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,150,356]" pageId="11" pageNumber="368">
<emphasis box="[199,363,258,284]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="368">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[378,511,258,284]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1675,1699]" captionTargetBox="[151,1408,381,1638]" captionTargetId="figure-116@11.[151,1436,380,1652]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 8. Thubdora vernaculella Park &amp; Karisch, 2021: A, Adult; B, Male genitalia, GU-3899/Karisch; B1, Aedeagus; C, Subgenital segments, in SDEI." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810524" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810524/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="368">Figs. 8B, B</figureCitation>
<figureCitation box="[511,522,258,284]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1300,1324]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,345,1276]" captionTargetId="figure-101@1.[151,1436,345,1276]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Topographical map of the region Northwest of Man, Black circles = collecting sites; inserted map: Ivory Coast with marked collecting area (arrow) (Openstreetmap, inserted map: Mapsland, CCA 3.0)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810508" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810508/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="368">1</figureCitation>
). Characterized by the uncus broadened apically, cucullus elongated, strongly upturned, slightly narrowed apically, slightly convex on costal margin; cornuti consisting of a low of setae medially, a long plate apically, and series of conical spines (these spines probably removed in this specimen)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
